name: I/O Extended 2017 OAU

venue.name: O.A.U Conference Center
venue.address_1: Road 8, Obafemi Awolowo University, Ife, Nigeria

description:
This is an extension of  the annual Google I/O conference that displays new innovations and technologies from Google.  It brings together thousands of tech enthusiasts and technology stakeholders to a single location for a super awesome time. We will be showing the keynote video and taking local developers through code labs in Firebase, Android (Kotlin), Tensorflow, API.AI and wait for it.................. a live Google Home demo! How would you rather spend your weekend?

Target audience:

•  Students

• Developers

• Designers

• Entrepreneurs

• Tech Enthusiasts and anyone who is interested in Google technologies.

name: DevFest SW Nigeria 2017
description:
GDG South-West DevFest 2017 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, codelabs, hackathon and more! We will be having developers from all around the south-west region of Nigeria in one place to experience the best of Google technology.

This year, GDG Ibadan would be hosting the GDGs in the region and GDG OAU is proud to be one of the collaborating GDGs

Please register here as this is the official attendee list. 

Website: http://devfestsw.gdg.ng

FAQs 

1. Why do I have to register twice? - This is primarily because we are collaborating with other GDGs for this event so meetup is not sufficient for event registration.
2. If I RSVP on meetup do I still need to register on the Eventbrite page? - Yes, you need to register on Eventbrite. See 1 above.
3. Do I need to register for this event? - Yes, while it's a free event, registration is compulsory.

name: SoC v2 Bootcamp General Class
description:
School of Code (SoC) is a software development mentoring Bootcamp organized by Google Developers Group OAU in collaboration with IEEEOAU and NACOSS OAU. Get mentored by experts in Data Science, Machine Learning, Web, Android programming, Networking & Security, and Hardware for FREE!!!. Yes, you read that right. It's 100% free.

We are seeking to mentor and help build the next generation of World Class Developers.

name: I/O Extended 2018 OAU

venue.name: O.A.U Conference Center
venue.address_1: Road 8, Obafemi Awolowo University, Ife, Nigeria

description:
Google I/O Extended OAU

Google I/O is an annual developer conference held by Google that brings together developers from around the globe for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and a first look at Google’s latest developer products. This year’s developer festival will be held May 8-10 at the Shoreline Amphitheatre in Mountain View, CA and we are extremely excited to host a GOOGLE I/O EXTENDED event here in Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife.

I/O Extended events help developers from around the world take part in the I/O experience.

We're going to discuss the latest news and releases from this year.

Target audience:
• Students
• Developers
• Designers
• Tech Enthusiasts and anyone who is interested in Google technologies.

Agenda:
Morning Session

Codelabs: 9:00am - 12 noon
# Flutter (9 - 10 am)
• Write Your First Flutter App, part 1& 2 - 43 mins

# Cloud (10 - 11 am)
• Integrating Machine Learning APIs - 25 mins
• Using the Natural Language API from Google Docs - 20mins

# ML & AI (11am - 12 Noon)
• Android & TensorFlow: Artistic Style Transfer - 22mins

Afternoon Session

General: 12:00 noon - 3:00pm

• Welcome Address - 5mins ( - 12:05)
• I/O keynote overview - 15mins (- 12:20)
• Interactive Panel session I (Developers) - 30mins (- 12:50)
- Everything you need to know about Flutter
- Android jetpack
- Kotlin
- PWA
- Instant Apps

• Lightning Talk I - Building the future of artificial intelligence for everyone - 10 mins (1:00PM)
• Lightning Talk II - Build with Google Pay - 10mins (1:10PM)
• Break - 30 mins (1:40PM) -
• Lightning talk III - Introduction to RxJava - 20 mins (2:00PM)
• Interactive Panel session II - 30mins (2:30PM )
- Introducing .app domains
- Google Lens
- Machine learning on mobile and TensorFlow
- Machine learning and medicine
- What's new in AR
• Lightning Talk IV - Introducing AIY: Do-it-yourself Artificial Intelligence - 10 mins (2:40)
• Opportunities for students with Google / Google Open Source - 10 mins (2:50)
• Announcement/Rounding off - 10mins (3:00PM)

The interested participant in the flutter codelab should follow these steps ahead of the class to fast track the labs:
1. Install flutter using this link
2. Install Dart and Flutter plugin on your editor here preferably android studio.

Kindly come early, if you need help setting it up on your laptop.

name: Cloud Study Jam - Learn Google Cloud Basics
description:
Learn the fundamentals of the Google Cloud Platform, how to run containers on it and how to use the platform for data engineering. Attendees get free access to the labs ($70+ value).

At the end of the event, every attendee will be getting Google-hosted badges that they can add to enhance their online portfolios or to simply show-off their cloud skill to employers.

Please make sure to bring your laptops and chargers since this will be a totally hands-on event.
